   JOHANNESBURG -  The Fair Finance Coalition of SA says communities bear the brunt of power cuts and should be more involved in the country's electricity planning processes. READ: SA's Electricity Crisis | Power cuts cause business instability The coalition also says Andre de Ruyter's corruption claims have caused uncertainty around the Just Energy Transition. It's worried the fallout could be an obstacle to the move to cleaner energy sources. Watch the full interview in the video below.  Former Eskom CEO Andre de Ruyter's graft claims has caused uncertainty about the Just Energy Transition. This is the concern of the African Climate Reality Project of the Fair Finance Coalition of SA. For more, #eNCA speaks to Leanne Govindsamy. #DStv403